<2ND_LINE>BC-Philippines-Fire,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fire Kills 10 In Philippines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CEBU CITY, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gas stove exploded and started a
pre-dawn apartment building fire Sunday that trapped and killed 10
people, including four children, police said.
   Investigators believe the stove exploded in the apartment of a
retired police officer in Cebu City. The officer and his wife were
among those killed, they said.
   The other fatalities included two families who also lived in the
building in the crowded Mambaling district of the city, which is
360 miles southeast of Manila.
   Most Philippine houses and apartments have iron grills over
windows to protect against burglars, but the grills stop people
from using windows to leave their apartments in an emergency.
Firefighters blame the grills for most fire deaths in the country.
   Firefighters said five other houses were destroyed or damaged by
the fire.
