in Norfolk, Va., said earlier the accident involved a truck and van.
   Hines said military investigators were looking into how the
accident happened and what caused it. Security personnel did not
witness it, he said.
   About 7,000 people, military personnel and civilian workers,
live on the base at the eastern tip of communist Cuba. The
facility, which is enclosed and surrounded by a minefield, serves
as the main training site for the Atlantic Fleet.
