<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Lotto America,0152</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Jackpot Swells To An Estimated $8.5 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A record Lotto America jackpot will
swell to $8.5 million for the May 7 drawing because no one
correctly picked all seven numbers in the latest drawing, a
spokesman of the Iowa-based game said Sunday.
   That's the the highest jackpot reached in the multi-state game
that had its first drawing on Feb. 13.
   A check of computers on Sunday revealed that no one purchased a
ticket for the numbers picked in Saturday night's televised drawing
for a $7.34 million jackpot, said spokesman Bret Voorhees. The
winning numbers were: 1, 3, 17, 19, 27, 29 and 34.
   However, Voorhees said, 22 tickets matched six of the numbers,
entitling each holder to a prize of $2,886, another 1,222 tickets
matched five numbers to win $99 each, and 21,823 players won $5
each by correctly picking four numbers.

